(16, 18, 'LEICA M\r\n', '<h3>MAXIMUM IMAGE QUALITY</h3>\r\n<h4>Because the best pictures tell the best stories</h4>\r\n\r\nThe new Leica M features a freshly-designed high resolution, 24-Megapixel CMOS sensor in full 35 mm format – the Leica Max 24-MP sensor.\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>SHARP IMAGES GUARANTEED</h3>\r\n<h4>In perfect focus</h4>\r\n\r\nThe classic rangefinder system plus two innovative focusing methods - Live View Zoom and Live View Focus Peaking - offer more creativity and control.\r\n\r\n<h3>FILMS WITH THE LEICA LOOK</h3>\r\n<h4>Intimate motion pictures, sharp images</h4>\r\n\r\nComplement your still images with professional video recordings using the 1080p, full-HD video recording feature. Exclusive with the new Leica M.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '<h4>Maximum image quality</h4>\r\n\r\nSuperior sharpness and the finest reproduction of detail. The Leica M features a newly-designed, high resolution, 24-Megapixel CMOS sensor in full 35 mm format – the Leica Max 24-MP sensor. When combined with the Leica Maestro image processor, only outstanding images are created. Additionally, the low noise performance makes the M ideal for available-light photography.\r\n\r\n<h4>Sharp images guaranteed</h4>\r\n\r\nThe classic rangefinder system offers fast, precise, crystal-clear focusing with superior accuracy. Two additional focusing methods allow for even more creativity. The new “Live View Zoom” enables up to 10A-magnification of the Live View display, and the “Live View Focus Peaking” automatically highlights sharp contours in red to provide simple focus control.\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>Motion pictures with Leica look</h4>\r\n\r\nThe unique quality of Leica lenses has been expanded into the 1080p, full-HD video recording feature of the Leica M. Complete control over exposure and capture settings enables photographers to complement their still images with professional video recordings, with the same look and quality inherent to Leica photography.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>Faster results</h4>\r\n\r\nThe combination of the Leica Max 24-MP sensor and Leica’s Maestro processor allows for an extremely high image-processing speed. A low buffer time lets you take photos in rapid succession, not missing a single shot. The processor’s several independent segments permit an incoming image to be processed while a previous one is still being written on the memory card.\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>Universal capabilities</h4>\r\n\r\nThe new Leica M is the first to feature Live View. Images are composed from material produced by the lens, granting you complete control over depth of field, exposure, framing and focusing. The M’s large, high-resolution 3" monitor with 920,000 pixels allows precise assessment of each potential image with regard to sharpness, exposure and colour.\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>Use in any weather conditions</h4>\r\n\r\nOur cameras are built to last a lifetime. Solid brass blanks and full-metal bodies from high-strength magnesium alloy and scratch-resistant Corning Gorilla® Glass make bodies and screens resistant to life’s little tumbles. Specially designed rubber seals protect the cameras from splashes, moisture, dust and uncooperative weather\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>For long-endurance missions</h4>\r\n\r\nLeica M’s new lithium-ion battery (1800 mAh) is high performance and rechargeable, ensuring that you are comfortably prepared for long shoots. One single charge guarantees a large number of exposures, which makes the M perfect for shooting in remote locations.\r\n\r\n<h4>Ergonomic handling</h4>\r\n\r\nThe Leica M combines the traditionally valued photographic functions of the M-System with state-of-the-art ergonomic features. With an ergonomically-positioned control wheel on the top plate, intuitive menu navigation and a newly-designed and user-friendly menu interface on the rear monitor, the photographer can concentrate on what’s essential – the images.\r\n\r\n<h4>Compatibility with Leica R-Lenses</h4>\r\n\r\nhe Leica M can take full advantage of almost all lenses in the Leica R-Lenses series, thanks to the new, state-of-the-art Leica R-Adapter. This extensive lens range includes various wide-angle, telephoto and macro lenses as well as a selection of zooms.\r\n\r\n\r\n', '<strong>Model Name: </strong>	Leica M (Typ 240) <br />\r\n	<strong>Manufacturer URL: </strong>	Manufacturer website <br />\r\n	<strong>Model Number: </strong>	M <br />\r\n	<strong>Camera Format: </strong>	Rangefinder\r\n	<strong>Retail Price: </strong>	$6950.00 <br />\r\n	<strong>Street Price: </strong>	$6,495.61 <br />\r\n	<strong>Date Available: </strong>	2012-02-15 <br />\r\n	<strong>Tripod Mount: </strong>	Yes <br />\r\n	<strong>Weight: </strong>	24.0 oz (680 g) <br />\r\n	<strong>includes batteriesSize: </strong>	5.5 x 3.1 x 1.7 in. (139 x 80 x 42 mm) <br />\r\n	<strong>Waterproof: </strong>	No <br />\r\n	<strong>Waterproof Depth: </strong>	n/a <br />\r\n	<strong>Sensor Type: </strong>	CMOS <br />\r\n	<strong>Sensor Manufacturer: </strong> <br />\r\n	<strong>Effective Megapixels: </strong>	24.0 <br />\r\n	<strong>Sensor Format: </strong>	35mm <br />\r\n	<strong>Sensor size: </strong>	864mm2 (36mm x 24mm) <br />\r\n	<strong>Approximate Pixel Pitch: </strong>	6.05 microns <br />\r\n	<strong>Focal Length Multiplier: </strong>	1.0x <br />\r\n	<strong>Aspect Ratio: </strong>	3: 2 <br />\r\n	<strong>Color Filter Type: </strong>	RGBG <br />\r\n	<strong>Anti Aliasing Filter: </strong> <br />\r\n	<strong>Self-Cleaning: </strong>	No <br />\r\n	<strong>Auto Focus:</strong>	No <br>\r\n	<strong>Auto Focus Type:</strong>	N/A (Manual focus with OVF/Live View with magnification, focus peaking) <br>\r\n	<strong>Auto Focus Assist Light?	n/a <br>\r\n	<strong>Manual Focus:</strong>	Yes <br>'),
(17, 9, 'Toshiba IK-WB16A-W', '<h4>2MP Wired or wireless Pan/Tilt Network Camera </h4>\r\n\r\nToshiba is offering the non-wireless IK-WB16A (shown) with PoE. The IK-WB16A-W is wireless but does not have PoE. The recording software allows you to view and record up to sixteen (16) IK-WB16A or IK-WB16A-W cameras. Simple, intuitive setup and playback provides complete surveillance. The IK-WB16A/A-W solution will show you how powerful, easy and cost effective an IP video surveillance system should be.\r\n\r\nACCESSORIES\r\nDATASHEETS\r\nDOWNLOADS/MANUALS\r\nINTEGRATION\r\nRESOURCE CALCULATOR\r\n', '<h4>.2 lux minimum illumination</h4>\r\n			<h4>4X digital zoom</h4>\r\n			<h4>Comes with free 16-CH recording software</h4>\r\n			<h4>Megapixel resolution (1600 x 1200) to capture small details and better identify subjects</h4>\r\n			<h4>Micro SD card slot for local recording</h4>\r\n			<h4>Pan range of -175° to +175°</h4>\r\n			<h4>Quad streaming MPEG4/JPEG video</h4>\r\n			<h4>Tilt range of +90° to -23°</h4>\r\n			<h4>Two versions available: PoE, non-wireless (IK-WB16A) and 802.11n wireless (IK-WB16A-W)</h4>\r\n			<h4>Two-way audio</h4>\r\n			<h4>Up to 30 frames per second</h4>\r\n			<h4>Warranty - 2 years parts and labor</h4>', '<strong>Audio In/Out :</strong>	MIC In (plug-in 3.3V, 200k); LINE OUT (1 Vms) 1 <br />\r\n			<strong>Effective Pixels :</strong>	1600 x 1200 <br />\r\n			<strong>Image Sensor :</strong>	1/3.2 inch CMOS 2MP <br />\r\n			<strong>IR Illuminators :</strong>	- <br />\r\n			<strong>Lens :</strong>	f=3.6mm F=1.8 <br />\r\n			<strong>Minimum Illumination :</strong>	0.2 lux / F1.8 (1/5s 8x) <br />\r\n			<strong></strong>Day/Night :</strong>	- <br />\r\n			<strong>Wide Dynamic Range :</strong>	- <br />\r\n			<strong>Dimensions :</strong> 5.0” (H) x 5.5” (D); (127mmx140mm) <br />\r\n			<strong>Environmental :</strong>	Housing Available <br />\r\n			<strong>Operation Temperature :</strong>	14° F to 122° F (-10° C to 50° C) <br />\r\n			<strong>Power Consumption